Document: AudioEffectStereoEnhance  
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectstereoenhance.rst  
Summary: Adds a stereo manipulation audio effect to an audio bus, controlling side channel gain and widening the stereo image.  

AudioEffectStereoEnhance inherits from AudioEffect and is used to manipulate stereo audio signals. It allows adjustment of the gain for side channels (left and right) and can widen the stereo image to create a more immersive audio experience. This effect is applied to an audio bus and can be configured through parameters exposed in the Godot editor. The primary use case is enhancing the spatial perception of audio in games or multimedia applications.
---CHUNK---
Document: AudioEffectStereoEnhance
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectstereoenhance.rst
Summary: Adjusts gain of the left and right channels, and makes mono sounds stereo through phase shifting.

AudioEffectStereoEnhance is an audio effect that modifies stereo channel balance and enhances stereo imaging by applying phase shifting to mono sources. It allows independent adjustment of left and right channel gains, enabling precise control over stereo width and depth. The effect works by detecting mono content (signals that are identical in both channels) and applying subtle phase differences to create a wider stereo image. This is particularly useful for enhancing the spatial characteristics of mono recordings or for creative audio processing in music production and game audio design.
