Document: AudioEffectStereoEnhance  
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectstereoenhance.rst  
Summary: Describes the properties and methods for controlling stereo enhancement effects in Godot, including pan pullout, surround widening, and time-based phase shifting.  

Property: pan_pullout (float) = 1.0  
Methods:  
- set_pan_pullout(value: float) → void  
- get_pan_pullout() → float  
Description: Gain of the side channels, if they exist. A value of 0 will downmix stereo to mono. Value can range from 0 to 4.  

Property: surround (float) = 0.0  
Methods:  
- set_surround(value: float) → void  
- get_surround() → float  
Description: Widens the stereo image through phase shifting in conjunction with time_pullout_ms. Just pans sound to the left channel if time_pullout_ms is 0. Value can range from 0 to 1.  

Property: time_pullout_ms (float) = 0.0  
Methods:  
- set_time_pullout(value: float) → void  
- get_time_pullout() → float  
Description: Widens the stereo image through phase shifting in conjunction with surround. Just delays the right channel if surround is 0. Value is in milliseconds, and can range from 0 to 50.